    <section>
        <h3>Research</h3>
        <p>I currently work on LLM inference systems and solver-based job scheduling. On the inference side, I'm a project lead on <a href="https://project-vajra.github.io/">Vajra</a>, studying hierarchical prefix caching and tensor exchange mechanisms. More broadly, I enjoy solving problems at the intersection of systems and
   programming languages.</p> 
        <p>Last summer I interned at Uber's Programming Systems Group, where I developed a parallel version of the RTA callgraph construction algorithm for the Go programming language.</p>
        <p>
          During my master's, I worked with
            <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/people/daan/">Daan Leijen</a>
          on prototyping an implementation of
            <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/perceus-garbage-free-reference-counting-with-reuse/">Perceus memory management</a> for OCaml.
        </p>
        <p>
          During my undergrad I was part of <a
          href="http://prod.tinker.cc.gatech.edu/" target="_blank">TINKER
          lab</a> where I was advised by <a
          href="https://www.scs.gatech.edu/people/thomas-conte"
          target="_blank">Prof. Thomas Conte</a> and <a
          href="https://www.cc.gatech.edu/people/jeffrey-young"
          target="_blank">Dr. Jeff Young</a>. While there, I wrote a
          space-efficient implementation of the quantum verification of matrix
          products (QVMP) algorithm.
        </p>

